<SLUG> BC-TURBODYNE-STOP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NASDAQ HALTS TURBODYNE STOCK TRADING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Trading in shares of Turbodyne Technologies was
halted Thursday on the Nasdaq stock exchange, one day after a
European exchange said it will punish the company for allegedly
issuing false and misleading press releases.
</P>
<P>
   Brussels-based Easdaq, Nasdaq's European counterpart, halted
trading in Turbodyne on Wednesday until Feb. 3 after an
investigation by its surveillance unit reportedly uncovered the
alleged wrongdoing. Easdaq said it is considering removing
Turbodyne from the exchange altogether.
</P>
<P>
   The Wednesday halt triggered an automatic stoppage on Nasdaq on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   In its written statement, Easdaq did not identify which
Turbodyne press releases contained the purportedly false or
misleading data but noted that the material was market-sensitive,
meaning it could have influenced investors to buy or sell the
stock.
</P>
<P>
   Turbodyne spokesman Peter Weichselbraun said he did not know
which statements Easdaq alleged were false. Weichselbraun said his
company has been in regular contact with the exchange since October
1998, when a short-selling investor claimed the company owned no
valuable technology.
</P>
<P>
   That claim, by New York-based trader Manuel Asesnio, prompted
Easdaq to request numerous documents from Turbodyne, Weichselbraun
said. ``But it seemed that we did not supply all Easdaq wanted to
see,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Turbodyne manufactures aluminum castings for the automobile
industry and has developed what it says are pollution-reduction
turbochargers for internal-combustion engines. The company in the
past year has announced several retrofitting deals for municipal
buses, mostly in European cities, but continues to generate nearly
all of its revenues from its castings business.
</P>
<P>
   Before the halt in trading, Turbodyne stock closed Wednesday at
$5.34375 per share. Its 52-week high is $17.12, set in July.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
