<SLUG> BC-BKN-CASSTEVENS-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JUST A LITTLE INDECISIVE, AREN'T WE? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DAVID CASSTEVENS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dear Antonio:
</P>
<P>
   So, what's up?
</P>
<P>
   I was in our office Thursday reading the sports wire when the
strangest thing happened. The AP moved an advisory: ``The Antonio
McDyess news'' ``conference scheduled for 3 p.m. in Denver has been
rescheduled for 5:30''.``''
</P>
<P>
   Now, we learn it has been postponed indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
   How long is indefinitely?
</P>
<P>
   What's the delay?
</P>
<P>
   Did a snowstorm hit Denver?
</P>
<P>
   Getting cold feet?
</P>
<P>
   This was supposed to be a done deal. Jerry Colangelo conceded as
much through clenched teeth Wednesday night. Danny Ainge looked
like he was ready to cry.
</P>
<P>
   Everybody said your mind was made up. Your friends and your
agents convinced you that you belong back in Denver. The money the
Nuggets have offered is less than you could make with the Suns.
</P>
<P>
   But money isn't everything.
</P>
<P>
   Neither is winning, I guess.
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets aren't the Broncos, or the Rockies or the Avalanche.
There must be a comfort level playing for the No. 4 pro team in
town.
</P>
<P>
   That must have been some scene at McNichols Arena, with people
sitting there, expectantly, waiting, glancing at their watches,
wondering as time passed, ``What's going on? Where ``is'' he?''
</P>
<P>
   That's like the groom not showing up for his wedding. How mad is
Dan Issel? The Nuggets GM must feel like the father of the bride.
</P>
<P>
   What did you tell him?
</P>
<P>
   What's going on?
</P>
<P>
   I can't remember anything quite like this. But then Thursday was
like no other day in NBA history.
</P>
<P>
   Karl Malone re-signed with Utah and ``cried.'' The world
champion Chicago Bulls disbanded. It was like watching the breakup
of the Soviet Union. Scottie Pippen went to Houston. In return, the
Bulls got Roy Rogers, who I thought was dead, and a horse to be
named later.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen will join Charles Barkley in Houston. Barkley reportedly
signed with the Rockets while playing out of a sand trap at the Bob
Hope Classic in Palm Springs. The Chuckster will get $1 million
this season. And two strokes per side.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Rodman, who is either married or single, confirmed he
will play this season, too. Maybe. Somewhere. Sometime. He will
discuss his future tonight on TV with Jay Leno.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday, the Suns signed Luc.
</P>
<P>
   Today, they're praying they can close the deal and acquire the
letter ``k.''
</P>
<P>
   With you in Denver, the Suns know they need Luc Longley and Luck
_ and Tom Gugliotta _ if they hope to stay competitive.
</P>
<P>
   But now, the Suns don't know ``what'' to do. Because they
``still'' don't know what ``you're'' going to do.
</P>
<P>
   Do you know?
</P>
<P>
   Can't you decide?
</P>
<P>
   Gugliotta flew to Phoenix on Thursday night. Do you expect the
Suns to stall the Minnesota free agent while you try to make up
your mind? Imagine Bryan and Jerry Colangelo and Gugliotta seated
around a table after a big Italian dinner.
</P>
<P>
   Gugliotta: ``Wonderful. I'm stuffed. Well, where do I sign?''
</P>
<P>
   Bryan: ``Tom, how about coffee?''
</P>
<P>
   Gugliotta: ``No, thanks.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Another dessert?''
</P>
<P>
   What's with you, Antonio? You know what Denver's offer is. Are
you having second thoughts because the Nuggets didn't tell you they
were renouncing the rights to your friend, LaPhonso Ellis? Is
``that'' what this is about?
</P>
<P>
   What do you want? Do you want to play in Phoenix? If so, a lot
of fans here would tell you to forget it. If you're this
indecisive, this uncommitted, then stay in Denver. The Suns would
be better off without you.
</P>
<P>
   I guess I'm more forgiving. To me, this is where you should be.
Where you belong. Remember when you arrived last year? Ainge said
you and Jason Kidd are the future of the Suns. ``They can grow
together for the next 10 years.''
</P>
<P>
   He is right.
</P>
<P>
   But it's your decision.
</P>
<P>
   Be a man. Make it. &QL; 
David Casstevens can be reached at david.casstevens(at)pni.com via
e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
