<SLUG> BC-SEX-CLUB-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE CLUB MAY BE THE ANSWER TO SEX IN THE WHITE HOUSE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By GUY P. BEACH  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The impeachment trial of President Clinton is of even greater
historical significance than that of O. J. Simpson.
</P>
<P>
   While the charges are grave _ perjury and obstruction of justice
_ it all began with inappropriate sexual conduct. Despite his track
record, inappropriate presidential sexual behavior was not invented
by Bill Clinton. Let us look at the record.
</P>
<P>
   While history books make rare mention, George Washington, the
Father of our Country, is said by some historians to have been very
much the amorous ladies man. Recently, new evidence strengthens the
case that Thomas Jefferson, a widower, fathered the illegitimate
children of Sally Heming, a mulatto slave. While DNA results are
not yet conclusive, it appears that something was up.
</P>
<P>
   In the 1884 presidential election, Democrat Grover Cleveland, an
absolute straight arrow in his public life, admitted to having
fathered an illegitimate child with a widow, Maria Crofts Halpin.
His Republican opponents coined the campaign slogan, ``Hey, ma,
where's my pa?'' an allusion to his paternity.
</P>
<P>
   After he won the election, the Democrats taunted, ``Gone to the
White House, ha, ha!''
</P>
<P>
   Woodrow Wilson had an extra-curricular liaison with a woman he
met while vacationing in Bermuda.
</P>
<P>
   And next comes the pre-JFK president credited with having the
lustiest libido, Warren Harding. He fathered an illegitimate child
with his No. 1 mistress of many years, Nan Britton. Their long and
torrid affair continued into Harding's White House years.
</P>
<P>
   In the book ``The Shadow of Blooming Grove'', author-historian
Francis Russell tells how Harding's trusted secret service agents
Walter Ferguson and James Sloan arranged assignations at the White
House.
</P>
<P>
   On one occasion, Mrs. Harding, usually referred to as the
Duchess and often described as a battle-ax, returned early,
suspecting that something was up. She stormed the cloak room next
to the Oval Office where the president and Britton were
passionately interfacing.
</P>
<P>
   The day was saved by agent Ferguson who blocked the door,
claiming that entry would violate Secret Service regulations and
jeopardize national security.
</P>
<P>
   FDR had affairs, the most notable of which was with Lucy Mercer
and extended over more than 20 years. Ms. Mercer was with the
president at his death in Warm Springs, Ga., on April 12, 1945.
</P>
<P>
   LBJ had a 21-year afair, (1948-69) with a Dallas woman, Madeline
Brown who produced a son Steven; plus countless transitory
encounters including, (so he boasted), interacting with a secretary
at his desk in the Oval Office.
</P>
<P>
   Long after his death, Lady Bird Johnson told a TV producer:
``You have to understand, my husband loved people; and half the
world are women. You don't think you could keep my husband away
from half the people?''
</P>
<P>
   Clearly, the impeachment and the trial in the Senate are a major
distraction from the important affairs of state. And clearly, all
this started with inappropriate sexual behavior. What, then, do we
do to end inappropriate sexual conduct among our politicos in
Washington?
</P>
<P>
   I submit that the solution lies in the development of an
electronic, miniaturized version of the Club which would be
attached to the zippers of all of our elected representatives. Each
Club would be controlled by an encryption device and the only
person with the code to unlock the Club would be the wife or
significant other, (either/or, not both), of the politico.
</P>
<P>
   Police departments all across America tell us that the Club is a
nearly foolproof way to prevent auto theft so why not transfer this
technology to zippers?
</P>
<P>
   I submit that the obvious choice to develop this zipper control
device is Bill Gates and his Microsoft team because Microsoft has
proven its ability to bring out new operating systems in short
development cycles and the very name Microsoft implies that it is
the right company.
</P>
<P>
   I also argue that if the Senate trial results in a plea bargain,
then President Clinton must agree to grant an unconditional pardon
enabling the immediate release of all people serving prison
sentences for perjury.
</P>
<P>
   (Guy Beach is a writer in Connecticut.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
