   HEALTH EDITORS
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   The Medical Tribune News Service has added a new feature,
CYBER-GUIDE, a weekly review of health sites on the World Wide Web,
written by medical editors and writers.
</P>
<P>
   Today's CYBER-GUIDE looks at:
</P>
<P>
   --MedlinePlus, the National Library of Medicine's link to its
journal database and a host of links to helpful health information.
(medlineplus.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/)
</P>
<P>
   --The American Medical Association site, which offers a mix of
consumer information and physician politics. (www.ama-assn.org)
</P>
<P>
   --Stanford University's Center for Narcolepsy, with information
on the condition and the latest treatments.
(www-med.stanford.edu/school/Psychiatry/narcolepsy/)
