<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Saturday, Jan. 23.
</P>
<P>
   HEILBRONER-ECONOMISTS (Undated) _ Ask economists in the baby
boom generation why they became economists, and any number will
give some credit to Robert L. Heilbroner. His 1953 book, ``The
Worldly Philosophers,'' which has sold nearly 4 million copies, is
a ``Profiles in Courage'' of the great thinkers who shaped modern
economics. So it is somewhat surprising to find Mr. Heilbroner
increasingly critical of the economists he helped inspire. They
have missed the point, he says. By Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
<P>
   BIBLE-J (Undated) _ In unscrambling the puzzle of the books
attributed to Moses, scholars have identified four narratives by
letters _ J, E, P, D. Now, after a dozen years of research, Richard
Elliott Friedman, a professor of Hebrew and comparative literature
at the University of California at San Diego, has tantalizingly
argued that the J narrative is far longer than the three others,
and actually extends considerably beyond the five Mosaic books. The
J source, he says, comprises a ``hidden book'' that is nearly 3,000
years old and that runs from Genesis to the First Book of Kings. By
Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
<P>
   ON-THE-ROAD (Undated) _ Consider them latter-day nomads. Or
maybe, come to think of it, more like venerable turtles, who carry
their homes on their backs. They are the hundreds of thousands of
elderly and retired people who take to life on the road, spending
all or much of the year wandering around North America in assorted
trailers, converted buses, campers and motor homes. (850 words)
</P>
<P>
   GLORIA-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Gloria'': Sidney Lumet,
director; with Sharon Stone and Jean-Luke Figueroa. Reviewed by
Lawrence Van Gelder.
</P>
<P>
   SMITHSON-RETIRE (Washington) _ The secretary of the Smithsonian
is retiring. By Irvin Molotsky.
</P>
<P>
   TONY-ODONNELL (New York) _ Rosie O'Donnell declines to be host
of the Tony Awards.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other
entertainment stories from our partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston
Globe, Cox News Service, Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle,
The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram,
Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle
Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
</TEXT>
