<P>
   OLY-SCANDAL (Undated) _ Another member of the International
Olympic Committee, Bashir Mohamed Attarabulsi of Libya, resigned,
one day before an IOC panel ends its investigation into the
widening Salt Lake City scandal. IOC President Juan Antonio
Samaranch said Attarabulsi, 61, a member since 1977, quit because
of revelations his son received college scholarships at Utah
schools from Salt Lake City boosters. By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SALTLAKECITY (Salt Lake City) _ Reaction of people in Salt
Lake City to the continuing scandal. By Kirk Johnson. (900 words)
