<P>
   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- The ugly little episode of the public
threat to Northeastern University by what the Globe refers to as
``one top Cellucci aide'' raises the question of political thuggery
by an administration that should consider itself lucky to have just
won re-election. By David Nyhan.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE &LR;   &UR; (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HANDYMAN-HOTTON (Undated) _ If windows are pitting on the
inside, they are defective and should be replaced gratis by the
manufacturer. By Peter Hotton.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-REVIEW (Undated) _ A sleeper of a car: the 1999 Protege ES,
powered by Mazda's 1.8-liter, 122-horsepower four-cylinder engine.
By Bill Griffith. (l and f coding.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Concealed behind the president's
much-criticized proposal to invest a portion of the Social Security
trust fund in the stock market was a little-noted plan to create a
``universal saving account'' for each child at birth. By David
Warsh.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ Investor should begin a long-term
dollar-cost-averaging program in a mutual fund invested in health
care stocks, specifically in a fund focusing on the pharmaceutical
and medical supplies end of the business. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
