without calling witnesses. Byrd says there aren't enough votes in
the Senate to convict the president of perjury and obstruction,
adding: ``Lengthening this trial will only prolong and deepen the
divisive, bitter and polarizing effect this sorry affair has
visited upon our nation.'' By JUDY HOLLAND and JENNIFER CORBETT
DOOREN.
