<P>
   ACTORS-WEBSITES (Undated) _ Actors like Leonardo DiCaprio,
Barbra Streisand to Arnold Schwarzenegger are among the stars who
in the past few months have acquired a new Hollywood status symbol:
an official Web site. By Nancy C. Hass.
</P>
<P>
   PARIS-HAUTE-FASHION (Paris) _ For those who are not in the know,
the haute couture collections separates the small-time fashion
player from those who can play the game at its liveliest. Which is
to say, at the big Paris houses _ Dior, Saint Laurent, Chanel _
where a custom-made suit without any detail to speak of costs about
$10,000. Throw in some embroidery, a chiffon blouse, maybe a coat
with feathers rising up irresistibly around the throat, and
suddenly madame is in a different stratosphere, calling for oxygen:
$30,000 $40,000 $50,000 even $100,000 for a dress. By Cathy Horyn.
Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BOOMERANG-KIDS (Undated) _ A lot of people in their 20s and 30s
have given up the privacy and independence of living on their own
to become roommates with Mom and Dad, in quarters where the cooking
is the ultimate in comfort food and the cable bill is usually
subsidized. By Rachel Lehman-Haupt. Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BRIDES-NIGHT-OUT (New York) _ Everyone knows the stuff of
bachelor parties: naked women bursting from cakes, stag films,
drunken toasts. Bachelorette parties, on the other hand, have a
reputation for cosmopolitans and frilly lingerie. But in a spirit
of equality of the sexes, bachelorette parties seem to be getting
more debauched. I have heard of bridesmaids shopping for sex toys
and of parties where women play ``truth or dare'' in a bar, asking
strange men to eat the candy necklaces from their throats. By Jenny
Lyn Bader.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ A professional designer looks at a
garden site, envisions what it could be, and draws up a list of
ideal plants. I look at a plant in a pot, envision it in the ground
somewhere, and go looking for a place to dig a hole. By Cass
Peterson.
</P>
