<P>
   ATTENTION: SPORTS AND NEWS EDITORS
</P>
<P>
   COMPREHENSIVE COX NEWSPAPERS SUPER BOWL ADVANCE BUDGET
</P>
<P>
   Cox newspapers will offer extensive coverage of Super Bowl
XXXIII. Both teams in the Sunday, Jan. 31 game are in cities in Cox
newspaper markets _ the Atlanta Journal-Constitution covers the
Atlanta Falcons and the Grand Junction Daily Sentinel covers the
Denver Broncos _ and the host city is also in a Cox market _ The
Palm Beach Post covers Miami. Extensive coverage begins Sunday,
Jan. 24 and will continue throughout the week leading up to the
game and conclude with a Super Bowl wrap-up package for papers of
Feb. 2. Reporters from Dayton and Austin will also file reports.
Here is a day-by-day advance budget to help News and Sports editors
plan their Super Bowl reports. Any changes in these advance budgets
will be noted in the daily Cox News Service budgets that will move
next week. Photo and graphic information will also be included on
the daily budgets. If you have questions or need more information,
call the CoxNet desk in Atlanta at 404 526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   FOR PAPERS OF SUNDAY, JAN. 24
</P>
