<P>
   FBN-SMITHS_ ATLANTA _ The Smith family chronicles: The Smiths,
who have owned the Falcons from the beginning, finally get their
chance to step on pro sports most glamorous stage. It has been an
often tumultuous trip, filled with the agony of being berated in
their own home town. There have been stupid decisions and at least
one good one, and it remains very ironic that the team, in the
aftermath of Rankin Sr.'s death, is 23-4 and Super Bowl bound.
(Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
