<P>
   SUPERBOWL-LADY _ MIAMI _ When the Super Bowl halftime show goes
off on Jan. 31, featuring a cast of 1,200 performers, from
high-school cheerleaders to pop stars Gloria Estefan and Stevie
Wonder, Maggi Rosenberg can finally take a rest. The
Wellington-based Rosenberg, a one-time professional dancer and now
a popular children's entertainer on the South Florida circuit _ her
stage name is ``Miss Maggi'' _ has been recruited to be the
rehearsal coordinator for the massive production. (It turns out
she's an old friend of one of the producers.) It's her job to coach
all the different performers and then bring them together on the
final day. Right now, she's still auditioning dancers. On Jan. 23,
she'll do her first major run-through, with up to 600 members of
the cast. On Jan. 30, she'll do a dress rehearsal with everybody.
And on Jan. 31 . . . it's showtime. (Passy, Palm Beach Post). 40.
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DAVIS _ MIAMI _ Focusing on matchup between running backs
Terrell Davis and Jamal Anderson (Woods, Palm Beach Post). WITH
ILLUSTRATION
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JAMAL _ MIAMI _ He set NFL record for carries this year. NFL
data says Jamal will be one-year wonder and wonOt be around in five
years. (Skolnick, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
