</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Accessory market is true to trends
 &HT;    By Danny C. Flanders
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ New designs in home decorating accessories take their
cue from furnishings. Whatever's hot in sofas, chairs and tables
spills over into lamps, pillows, frames and rugs.
</P>
<P>
   Some of today's most popular themes and motifs for furniture
manufacturers are retro, Asian and garden. And when it comes to
accessories, nowhere were those categories more evident than at
last week's Atlanta International Gift &AMP; Home Furnishings Market,
held at the wholesale complex AmericasMart.
</P>
<P>
   Even dogs _ and we don't mean bad merchandise _ seemed to show
up in packs, from the fine to the funky.
</P>
<P>
   Here are some of the newest products, which should be in area
stores by September.
</P>
<P>
   Danny C. Flanders writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
