<HEADER>
A4791 &Cx1f; taf-z
s l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-PARIS-HAUTE-FASHION-$     01-22 0361
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PARIS-HAUTE-FASHION-$ADV24-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
 
PARIS: two houses.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Playing to a packed front row of loyal and well-coiffed clients,
including Catherine Deneuve, Mrs. Blair and France Goldman _ a
relatively new haute couture customer from Florida, who attended
all the big shows with her husband, David _ Saint Laurent showed
his classic suits with sheer chiffon blouses. The colors were
vintage Saint Laurent, with lots of purple, peacock blue, vivid
pink and smoky brown mixed with black.
</P>
<P>
   For evening, there were mostly draped gowns in flowery chiffon
or silk crepe, one in white with dark feathers splashing over the
shoulders. It was a predictable collection, but with Saint
Laurent's influence everywhere these days, particularly at Jean
Paul Gaultier, it's hard to hold that against him.
</P>
<P>
   Most people think of Balmain as ``Oscar's show,'' and who at
Balmain can complain? Everyone who counts was there, from European
aristocrats to a couple of the Miller sisters, Alexandra Von
Furstenberg and Marie-Chantal, wife of Crown Prince Pavlos of
Greece, who was attending with her.
</P>
<P>
   As for the show, there were lots of cream- and sand-colored
jackets and slim pants; a lovely stone-colored cocktail ensemble
with a silvery beaded top, and a white caftan embroidered in
rustic, red-hued paisley. The collection had a light, young touch,
though it could have been a little less bread-and-butter correct
and more flesh-and-blood sexy.
</P>
<P>
   Coming out of the Balmain show, Mrs. Goldman, a blonde, who is
French-Canadian, gave her summary of the season. ``I liked
Jean-Paul Gaultier,'' she said. ``To me, his was one of the best
collections. And Christian Lacroix. I was a little disappointed
with Dior. Galliano has the atelier, all the backup and talent, but
I don't know what's happening to him. The last two collections have
been a disappointment.''
</P>
<P>
   Goldman, whose business is in metals and chemicals, was
obviously taking a keen interest in the whole thing. He had marked
the numbers he liked for his wife. ``Well, we have our fittings
tomorrow, and I think we have five,'' he said. ``There's something
in every line that we will probably buy.''
</P>
</TEXT>
