today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
YOYO-TOY (Los Angeles) _ In the ups-and-downs of the toy business,
who's to tell what contraption will catch the eye of a child? Now
the toy of the moment is a toy of the past, a relic from the bygone
days of jacks and marbles. Kids have rediscovered the yo-yo.By
Jenifer Hanrahan. 
. 
HOT-TIPS (Los Angeles) _ It's that time of year when you're forced
to see the damage done over the holidays. Sure, you could go cold
turkey and cut out all fats and frantically start gardening and
decorating to tone those muscles. And in those areas, Miz Hot Tips
has some stylin' suggestions. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 

