$70,000 in inducements to two African IOC members the night before
Sydney won the 2000 Games by two votes. Australia's senior IOC
member, who said he was not involved in the offer, acknowleged that
the inducement could be seen as a bribe and bring demands for
Sydney to be stripped of the games. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
