<SLUG> BC-HOT-TIPS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
POST-HOLIDAY STYLIN' GOES ON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It's that time of year when you're forced to see
the damage done over the holidays. You know, all of those See's
chocolates that you wolfed down when nobody was looking, the family
grazing fests with homemade pies and Christmas cookies that make
your thighs jiggle like Jell-O.
</P>
<P>
   Sure, you could go cold turkey and cut out all fats and
frantically start gardening and decorating to tone those muscles.
And in those areas, Miz Hot Tips has some stylin' suggestions
you'll find below.
</P>
<P>
   Or you could say to heck with the diet and buy into that cool
new line of clothing worn by Camryn Manheim of ABC's ``The
Practice.'' She's the classy plus-size actress who often is seen in
designs by Tamotsu, and soon will be appearing in fashion magazine
ads as the company's celebrity model.
</P>
<P>
   The new line will be called Hana, which means flower in
Japanese, and will include sporty separates in black and ivory made
of that trendy microfiber Tencel. Look for them soon at Nordstrom,
Bloomingdale's and Saks Fifth Avenue, and expect to pay about $80
to $170 per item.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING SOIREE: If you are of a mind to work off those holiday
calories, Miz Hot Tips suggests some mall-hopping to see what's
new, like the Art of Shopping exhibit at the Glendale Galleria,
Glendale. Included is the Rag Factory, a new boutique that puts art
on clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Topanga Plaza in Canoga Park also has an exhibit, ``The Making
of a First Lady.'' The exclusive collection of Jacqueline Kennedy
Onassis photos will be on display through Jan. 31 in the center
court.
</P>
<P>
   Or head out this weekend for the grand opening of Dancing on
Clouds at 1521 S. Robertson Blvd. in Los Angeles. The new store
specializes in dance and activewear for girls and teens.
</P>
<P>
   Then, on Feb. 13, the Fallbrook Mall in West Hills will hold its
12th annual children's beauty pageant. They have trophies for
babies and older kids, but you have to call (818) 340-5981 to
register.
</P>
<P>
   What if you're too lazy to get in the car?
</P>
<P>
   Try the QVC channel today, where fashion designer Nolan Miller
will host ``Extreme Shopping: Hollywood'' live at the historic
Hollywood Roosevelt Hotel.
</P>
<P>
   Other alternatives coming up are Neiman Marcus' new Refresh
catalog that focuses on health and beauty, and Nordstrom's new
online shopping catalog (Nordstrom.com) that debuts Feb. 15. Among
the 61,500 items will be Callaway golf clothing and Nordstrom's own
shoe designs.
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING PANACHE: You've avoided cleaning out the flower beds
in the front yard for way too many reasons, including not having
the right tools? Miz Hot Tips spotted a fashion-forward garden tool
kit in dark green with floral-trimmed handles on the trowel, hand
rake, clippers and edgers that match the spiffy pink gardening
gloves. Sure to make the neighbors jealous, it's priced at $22.50
in the Paragon spring catalog, (800) 343-3095.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC ON HIS MIND: Fashion's latest hero, Tommy Hilfiger, is
sponsoring the Rolling Stones ``No Security'' tour that comes to
Southern California Feb. 9-11, so naturally he's dressing the
famous band with a new clothing logo. It incorporates the Rolling
Stones' tongue and the Tommy Hilfiger flag, and you can find it on
T-shirts and other stuff at the concert and Macy's stores. &QL; 
ENDIT &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
