   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-POPE (Mexico City) _ Pope John Paul, seeking to roll back
Protestant inroads in the past 20 years, will pay homage to the
Virgin of Guadalupe, the peasant girl who paved the way for
Catholicism throughout Latin America. By Diego Ribadeneira and
Richard Chacon. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-KIDNAPS (Belgrade) _ KLA abducts five elderly Serbs in
Kosovo, setting up the potential for another round of retribution.
By Susan Milligan. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   STOLEN-ART (Undated) _ Chief Sicilian detective for stolen
antiquities is under investigation for involvement in illegal
antiquities trade. By Walter V. Robinson. 500 words. (i and e
coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACHMENT (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-QUESTIONS (Washington) -- A key Democratic senator says
he will lead an effort to dismiss impeachment charges against
President Clinton next week. By Bob Hohler. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-MOTIONS (Washington) -- GOP scrambles to prove that Sen.
Robert C. Byrd's stature does not automatically grant him power to
proclaim the end of ``this sad and sorry time.'' By Anne E.
Kornblut. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-PUNISHMENT (Washington) -- Is impeachment meant to be
punishment or eviction? Senators have to decide this to figure out
how to vote. By Adam Pertman. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FEDERAL-SURPLUS (Washington) _ President Clinton's ambitious
State of the Union agenda hinges on $4.3 trillion in surplus funds
over next 15 years. By Adam Pertman. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MA-NURSING (Boston) _ Nursing registration board chairman
defends proposed regulations. Union says they're likely to make
nurses vulnerable when standing up for professional standards. By
Richard A. Knox. 900 words.
</P>
