<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Jan. 23. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
CARCRAZY (Phoenix) - Every January, Phoenix and Scottsdale go
bonkers for old cars. You see them everywhere, beautifully restored
or ratty original, classic cars parked on the street corners with
for-sale signs, cruising past on the highway _ muscle cars, classic
cars, even valuable Ferraris _ they just come out of the woodwork.
It's most evident in the Republic classified, where the typical
single column of classic-car ads suddenly turns into two full
pages. Or more. On the auction site, bidding reaches a fevered
pitch as people vie for their hearts' desires. At the automobilia
auction in the morning, where people pay top dollar for old
automotive artworks, toys and collectibles, you see such sights as
a veteran auctioneer holding up a small metal car. ``What am I bid
for this exquisite Rolls-Royce Dinky toy, only missing one
headlight?'' It sold for 50 bucks. By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move
in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
IMPEACH-AZNOTES (Phoenix) - What folks are thinking about the
impeachment of President Clinton. By JULIE AMPARANO. Stry will move
in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
IMPEACH-BOREDOM (Phoenix) - The impeachment trial is a sad and
disreputable sight. That is why most of us Americans simply cannot
watch the damn thing. It is why we flip the channel to basic cable,
since that seems to be the only way to avoid it. Let me watch
Animal Planet or the Travel Channel. Please. We are no longer
citizens, but sports fans. In this corner, with leather masks, the
tag team of Bill Bennett and Pat Buchanan; in the other corner,
wearing capes, is Lanny Davis and Michael Kinsley. They will debate
to the death. Unfortunately, the death involved is the one we die
of boredom. By RICHARD NILSEN. Story will move in the ``K''
category. Embargoed for Sunday, Jan. 24. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
