 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  Friday, Jan. 22, 1999 
  
 
Editors: 
 
Eds.: In a story slugged COCAINE-BUST that moved Thursday, Jan. 21,
the story should have said that the seizure of 9,500 pounds of
cocaine at the Port of Houston was the largest in Texas by the U.S.
Coast Guard. The largest cocaine bust in the state was made by the
Department of Public Safety, which found 18,350 pounds of of the
drug in Harlingen on Oct. 4, 1989. 
 
 
Houston Chronicle  
 

