<P>
   IMPEACHMENT TRIAL
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-CONFUSION _ WASHINGTON _ What's next in the Senate
trial? No one seems to know for sure, and conflicting information
is coming every day from normally well-organized Senate leaders.
(Carr, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/IMPEACH-GADEL _ What questions did Cleland and Coverdell ask
and what might they illustrate. (Foskett, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-CLOCK _ WASHINGTON _ The Ohio Clock is an impeachment
crossroads. This clock, in a corridor outside the Senate chamber,
is a traditional meeting place for the press and politicians.
(Dart, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   A Cox photo will be placed in the National folder on the Cox
server.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GOP _ WASHINGTON _ The Republican National Committee, trying to
regain its political footing after last year's setback, appeared to
soften its anti-abortion stance Friday. Newly relected chairman Jim
Nicholson, outlining the party's priorities through the 2000
election, deliberatedly left out abortion, in consultation with GOP
congressional leaders. Ironically, the RNC inched away from banning
abortion, one of its bedrock issues since Ronald Reagan's
presidency, as thousands of anti-abortion marchers staged their
annual protest against the Supreme Court ruling legalizing
abortion. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   GOVERNORS _ WASHINGTON _ With their state treasuries
overflowing, governors from coast to coast called this month for
more civility and cooperation between diverse ethnic groups and
political parties. A Cox Newspapers review of inaugural or ``state
of the state'' addresses this month by more than 40 of the 50
governors showed that three themes _ less confrontation, higher
spending on education, and lower taxes _ popped up in almost every
major speech. (Mollison, Cox News Service 900). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   w/GOVERNORS-QUOTES _ Best bites from the governors' speeches.
</P>
<P>
   GOVERNORS-DATA _ Graphics material on budget trends. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Cox photos for this story will be placed in the National folder
on the Cox server.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ A deposition of direct testimony by
Paul Maritz, a Microsoft vice president and key Internet broswer
figure, is released in the federal antritrust trial. (Glass, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-POPE _ MEXICO CITY _ The arrival of Pope John Paul II in
Mexico. Developing. (Ferriss, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   IOC-BRIBERY _ LONDON _ When the austere, powerful and heretofor
mysterious International Olympic Committee gathers for its meeting
in Lausanne, Switzerland, today (Jan. 23), it will find itself
under the most intense microscope since its inception. A scandal
that broke over the 2002 Olympic Games in Salt Lake City, Utah, is
spreading like a cancer that shaking the foundation of the Olympic
movement like nothing since the Ben Johnson steroids debacle.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moved Thurs., Jan. 21, in both the International and Sports
categories.
</P>
<P>
   ATTN: Atlanta OUT.
</P>
<P>
   PANAMA-TRAVEL _ PANAMA CITY, Panama _ In the Panama Canal, ships
are raised like toys, step by step, through three sets of locks to
a height of 85 feet above sea level, on their way from the Atlantic
to the Pacific and back again. Each passage requires 52 million
gallons of fresh water to equalize the water levels in these locks.
Nearly 85 years after its completion, these 50 miles of man-made
ditch are still an engineering wonder to behold, and the most
popular tourist attraction in this Ohio-sized country. (Emling, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Cox photos for this story will be placed in the International
and Travel folders on Cox Server.
</P>
