<P>
   JASPERDEATH-AWARD _ JASPER, Texas _ Seven months after the
dragging death of James Byrd Jr. and four days before the start of
the capital murder case for the first of three suspects charged in
49-year-old's brutal death, members of the Byrd family received a
national honor for the way they responded to the tragedy. (Lufkin
Daily News).
</P>
<P>
   OCEANS _ LOS ANGELES _ Pollution of the oceans is beginning to
come back to haunt humans. Bacterial and viral contamination of
shellfish and other fish is leading to growing numbers of foodborne
outbreaks. The latest out of the American Association for the
Advancement of Science's annual meeting in Los Angeles. (Seabrook,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   USSATLANTA _ NORFOLK, Va. _ Navy ship named for the largest city
in Georgia is being decommissioned. Will include interviews.
(Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TORNADO _ Tornadoes ripped across Arkansas, Tennessee,
Mississippi and Louisiana. At least eight people are dead.
Including possible severe weather in Georgia and other areas. Gita
Smith. w/photos.
</P>
<P>
   w/CLARK _ The downtown of historic Clarksville, Tenn., was hard
hit by the storm. (Davis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH MAP
AND PHOTOS
