NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, JANUARY 23
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NY-IMPEACH-RALLY-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Jan. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Jan. 19,
about anti-impeachment rallies organized across the country by
People for the American Way, a liberal advocacy group,
misidentified Barbara Handman, who organized a rally in New York at
the headquarters of 1199, the National Health and Human Services
Union. She is vice president of People for the American Way and
director of its New York office, not director of the union local.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SCHIER-NYT (moved on Thursday, Jan. 21)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Ernest Schier, director of the National Critics
Institute at the Eugene O'Neill Theater Center in Waterford, Conn.,
sent by the New York Times News Service on Thursday, Jan. 21,
misstated the date of his death. It was Jan. 12, not last Tuesday.
</P>
